The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, January 31, 2004 				 CESC books light up with Rs 40cr profit
 OUR BUREAUX																								Jan. 30: CESC, the RPG-controlled power utility, has registered a Rs 40 crore net profit in the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 against a net loss of Rs 40 crore in the corresponding period last year. Net sales increased 9.22 per cent to Rs 533 crore compared with Rs 488 crore last year.																								In the nine months period net sales grew to Rs 1,832 crore (Rs 1,632 crore). Net profit stood at Rs 53 crore as against a loss of Rs 75 crore last year. Earnings per share has become positive at Rs 2.27 per share.  ONGC net drops 																								Oil and Natural Gas Corp (ONGC) today reported a 33.7 per cent drop in its net profit to Rs 1,718.53 crore in the third quarter ended December 31, 2003. Total income declined to Rs 7,572.56 crore (Rs 7,890.99 crore). It has declared an interim dividend of Rs 14 per share.																								CMD Subir Raha said, Our third quarter net profit is lower as we had to provide Rs 3000 crore to downstream retailing companies for subsidising LPG and kerosene.																								MRPL has reported a net profit of Rs 40 crore in the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 against a net loss of Rs 130 crore year-on-year. Turnover was up at Rs 3,357 crore (Rs 2,368 crore).  HPCL net zooms																								Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd (HPCL) has posted a 134.62 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 775.71 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 compared with Rs 330.62 crore in the same period last fiscal. Net sales were up at Rs 14,259.45 crore (Rs 14,219.89 crore). 																								During the nine-month period ended December, net profit was Rs 1,376.89 crore (Rs 903.24 crore) while net sales were Rs 41,272.72 crore (Rs 38,786.91 crore). BPCL net soars 108%																								Bharat Petroleum Corp (BPCL) today reported a 107.85 per cent jump in its net profit for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 at 484.3 crore as against Rs 233 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.																								Net sales during the quarter was up at Rs 13,762.7 crore as against Rs 12,647.5 crore reported in the same period last year.
